          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".A PU-O2 source containing 1.092E-02 g of",
                " fissionable material on a 0.13 milli-m thick",
                " platinum backing. the isotopic composition was -",
                "  PU-242  89.37 %          PU-241  0.93 %",
                "  PU-240   4.57 %          PU-239  5.13 %"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The data was obtained from an extrapolation",
                " to 100 per cent fission fragment detection",
                " efficiency based on the results of 15 runs."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The only impurity isotope contributing to",
                " spontaneous fission neutrons was Pu-240. since",
                " this isotope has a nu-bar value very similar to",
                " that of Pu-242 the associated correction is",
                " negligibly small.",
                ".the fission fragment detection efficiency,",
                " deduced from a measurement of the total neutron",
                " output of the sample ( corrected for (alpha,n)",
                " reactions ) varied between 62 and 88 per cent,",
                " as the gas pressure was varied. an extrapolation",
                " to 100 per cent efficiency was made."
              ]
            }
          ],
